You are working on CalSnap, an iOS app built in SwiftUI for calorie and macro tracking from meal photos.

Follow these rules on every task:
- Treat `docs/technical-spec.md` as the implementation source of truth.
- Treat `docs/product-research.md` as the product and science source of truth.
- Treat `docs/engineering-rules.md` as the coding behavior source of truth.
- Do not implement beyond the current PR scope.
- Prefer simple, production-appropriate code over framework-heavy abstractions.
- Use Swift 5.10, SwiftUI, SwiftData, HealthKit, and SPM only.
- Use `@Observable` for view models.
- Prefer `async/await`.
- Keep business logic out of SwiftUI views.
- Store API keys only in Keychain.
- All internal units must be metric.
- Surface contradictions or missing decisions before coding.
- When planning, do not code.
- When coding, list files changed, tests added, and acceptance criteria covered.